comment: A walk as word corresponds to the sequence of vertices in a walk in a pseudograph. This variant of ~ wlkiswwlks2 does not require ` G ` to be a simple pseudograph, but it requires the Axiom of Choice ( ~ ac6 ) for its proof. Notice that only the existence of a function ` f ` can be proven, but, in general, it cannot be "constructed" (as in ~ wlkiswwlks2 ). (Contributed by Alexander van der Vekens, 21-Jul-2018.) (Revised by AV, 10-Apr-2021.)
